transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, good afternoon. This is Harvey Micklin checking Austin, Texas.

Speaker 1: I just placed an order for the Viagra ATV, I think,

Speaker 2: and I just wanted to verify that that was what I actually ordered.

Speaker 1: Sure. Hold on one second. I can help you out.

Speaker 2: Sure.

Speaker 1: Okay, Harvey, can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 2: July 12, 1949.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much. Yes.

Speaker 2: Yes, I see you ordered a quantity of 25, 50 milligrams of the EGV.

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's what I was hoping that I ordered, yeah.

Speaker 2: And that's not on a reorder or anything because I want to try these first

Speaker 1: and then see if I want to get on the regular schedule or not.

Speaker 2: Okay, yes, so it does look like the doctor put you on refills every two months,

Speaker 1: which you do not have to have.

Speaker 2: What a lot of people like to do is just go ahead and pause that for six months.

Speaker 1: That way it keeps you locked in at your price point and just allows you

Speaker 2: and keeps your prescription active so you can just call in whenever you need a refill.

Speaker 1: If you want, I can pause that for you.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I'd rather just call in for a refill.

Speaker 1: That's not a problem. Yeah, that makes sense.

Speaker 2: I'll pause you until July 31, 2026.

Speaker 1: Okay, that sounds great.

Speaker 2: Perfect. You're all set, Harvey.

Speaker 1: Well, thank you very much. I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: No problem. Have a great day.

Speaker 1: You too. Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
